00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:17,623 --> 00:00:19,911
<i>[Revolutionary Love]</i>

3
00:00:20,606 --> 00:00:22,524
Our Gangsu Group...

4
00:00:22,524 --> 00:00:25,591
<i>[Episode 7]</i>
cherishes our cleaning employees.

5
00:00:26,176 --> 00:00:27,954
We are considerate of them.

6
00:00:32,811 --> 00:00:35,972
Therefore, CEO Byun Gang Su...

7
00:00:36,557 --> 00:00:40,856
has decided to not use external
contractors for cleaning services.

8
00:00:40,856 --> 00:00:42,429
He will hire them directly.

9
00:00:42,429 --> 00:00:46,576
He decided to make that
announcement on this very day.

10
00:00:46,576 --> 00:00:49,409
What? Is that true?

11
00:00:49,985 --> 00:00:51,417
Hyuk didn't mention that.

12
00:00:51,417 --> 00:00:52,912
I never heard that.

13
00:00:55,182 --> 00:00:56,683
Hyuk.

14
00:00:56,683 --> 00:00:58,380
- What's going on?
- Hey.

15
00:00:58,380 --> 00:01:00,445
What's happening?

16
00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:03,087
Is it true?

17
00:01:03,087 --> 00:01:05,200
Is that true?

18
00:01:05,881 --> 00:01:08,603
Changing temporary
employees to full-time?

19
00:01:08,603 --> 00:01:10,822
All of those employees?

20
00:01:12,834 --> 00:01:15,274
CEO Byun Gang Su.

21
00:01:15,274 --> 00:01:20,560
I truly thank you for this
very meaningful decision.

22
00:01:23,066 --> 00:01:24,989
- It's true?
- Really? Oh my.

23
00:01:24,989 --> 00:01:27,405
CEO Byun Gang Su!
Thank you!

24
00:01:27,405 --> 00:01:29,634
Thank you!

25
00:01:29,634 --> 00:01:31,730
Give him a round of applause!

26
00:01:37,674 --> 00:01:40,243
That little punk.

27
00:01:43,414 --> 00:01:45,490
CEO Byun! CEO!

28
00:01:45,490 --> 00:01:47,406
Is that true?

29
00:01:47,406 --> 00:01:49,983
Please give us a comment.

30
00:01:51,652 --> 00:01:53,007
Just one comment.

31
00:01:53,007 --> 00:01:55,984
Hyuk, you little rascal.

32
00:02:06,058 --> 00:02:07,456
Come here.

33
00:02:07,456 --> 00:02:12,143
Hey, you insane little punk.

34
00:02:13,775 --> 00:02:16,456
When did I ever decide that?

35
00:02:17,086 --> 00:02:20,568
Who said you could say that?

36
00:02:22,205 --> 00:02:24,359
They clean the Gangsu Group building.

37
00:02:24,359 --> 00:02:27,195
It's strange that they're not
employees of Gangsu Group.

38
00:02:27,195 --> 00:02:29,343
So, what?

39
00:02:29,343 --> 00:02:32,127
You dare to protest your
father's company?

40
00:02:32,127 --> 00:02:34,126
I wasn't there as your son.

41
00:02:34,126 --> 00:02:36,139
I was there as the cleaner,
Byun Hyuk.

42
00:02:36,139 --> 00:02:37,937
So...

43
00:02:37,937 --> 00:02:40,588
you're going to become
a fighter for rights overnight?

44
00:02:40,588 --> 00:02:41,902
It's not that.

45
00:02:41,902 --> 00:02:43,247
I know what's going on.

46
00:02:43,247 --> 00:02:45,576
The main contractor abuses
its power over contractors.

47
00:02:45,576 --> 00:02:47,737
Service contractors
abuse power over the employees.

48
00:02:47,737 --> 00:02:51,396
It's never-ending.
That's how it is.

49
00:02:51,396 --> 00:02:53,318
I know it all too.

50
00:02:55,486 --> 00:02:59,950
You don't know what you're talking about.

51
00:03:07,530 --> 00:03:10,068
What were you doing?
What were you doing!

52
00:03:10,068 --> 00:03:13,111
- Father!
- You should've stopped it!

53
00:03:13,111 --> 00:03:14,818
Stop it, Father!

54
00:03:14,818 --> 00:03:17,277
Oh, you'd better let go.
Let go of me!

55
00:03:17,277 --> 00:03:18,657
Don't hit Jae Hoon, please.

56
00:03:18,657 --> 00:03:20,328
- Just hit me.
- Hey!

57
00:03:20,328 --> 00:03:22,548
- Don't hit other people.
- Let go!

58
00:03:22,548 --> 00:03:25,137
I said don't hit others!

59
00:03:45,566 --> 00:03:48,210
How dare you?

60
00:03:58,911 --> 00:04:00,281
Why, you little...

61
00:04:00,281 --> 00:04:05,074
All right, let's both die here today.

62
00:04:05,074 --> 00:04:06,403
You rascal.

63
00:04:06,403 --> 00:04:08,663
Get up now, punk.

64
00:04:08,663 --> 00:04:11,153
I... I have something to say.

65
00:04:11,153 --> 00:04:12,868
Joon.

66
00:04:18,004 --> 00:04:19,500
Who are you?

67
00:04:21,425 --> 00:04:23,995
Hey, Secretary Park.
What were you doing!

68
00:04:23,995 --> 00:04:25,019
Please leave.

69
00:04:25,019 --> 00:04:27,774
Just a moment.
I just need one moment.

70
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:35,209
Didn't Gangsu Group contract out the
cleaners in order to save labor costs?

71
00:04:35,209 --> 00:04:38,850
But, when the contractors hire cleaners,
you pay a high commission fee.

72
00:04:38,850 --> 00:04:44,954
Meanwhile, the cleaners get poor
benefits, pay, and unfair dismissal.

73
00:04:44,954 --> 00:04:48,266
So? What does that
have to do with me?

74
00:04:48,266 --> 00:04:50,199
What I'm trying say is...

75
00:04:50,199 --> 00:04:55,221
if Gangsu Group hired cleaners directly,
there would be no difference in cost.

76
00:04:55,221 --> 00:04:57,940
Also, the cleaning staff
wouldn't suffer under contractors.

77
00:04:57,940 --> 00:05:02,538
If the costs are the same,
why would I have to do such a thing?

78
00:05:02,538 --> 00:05:05,922
"A person's heart is more
important than money."

79
00:05:05,922 --> 00:05:08,120
"To create employees who care"

80
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:10,319
"owners must first
understand their hearts."

81
00:05:10,319 --> 00:05:14,718
Third line on page 470 of your
book, "Human Management."

82
00:05:14,718 --> 00:05:17,682
Didn't you write that yourself, CEO Byun?

83
00:05:20,641 --> 00:05:21,911
You read my book?

84
00:05:21,911 --> 00:05:24,552
Between employees
who think of it as their company

85
00:05:24,552 --> 00:05:27,331
and those who consider it temporary...

86
00:05:27,331 --> 00:05:30,283
who do you think would work harder?

87
00:05:36,293 --> 00:05:39,067
Are you a cleaner, as well?

88
00:05:39,067 --> 00:05:42,093
No, I got fired yesterday.

89
00:05:42,093 --> 00:05:45,317
Then I have no reason to listen to you.

90
00:05:45,317 --> 00:05:50,548
You should work here, at the least,
to request something from me.

91
00:05:51,887 --> 00:05:53,617
You're nothing here.

92
00:05:53,617 --> 00:05:58,105
You can talk all you want and show off,
but what's the use?

93
00:05:58,105 --> 00:06:04,115
If you're so great,
you should become an employee here.

94
00:06:04,115 --> 00:06:08,680
Full-time employment is silly.

95
00:06:10,810 --> 00:06:11,846
What?

96
00:06:11,846 --> 00:06:15,567
You work so hard to get it,
but you lose your job in your 40s.

97
00:06:15,567 --> 00:06:21,004
People waste time, money,
and their lives just to get that job.

98
00:06:39,637 --> 00:06:41,384
You're a coward.

99
00:06:42,576 --> 00:06:44,471
A coward?

100
00:06:45,718 --> 00:06:47,593
- Are you talking about me?
- Yes.

101
00:06:47,593 --> 00:06:50,473
You're scared and running
before even starting.

102
00:06:50,473 --> 00:06:55,557
You have lots of excuses,
and you haven't even tried.

103
00:06:56,502 --> 00:06:58,446
Coward.

104
00:07:14,516 --> 00:07:15,999
Joon, I'm so sorry.

105
00:07:15,999 --> 00:07:17,696
I'll apologize on behalf of my father.

106
00:07:17,696 --> 00:07:19,391
Joon.

107
00:07:46,963 --> 00:07:49,348
Was this it?

108
00:07:49,348 --> 00:07:51,915
Your plan to do whatever you could?

109
00:07:52,459 --> 00:07:56,244
At least, I didn't die.

110
00:07:57,108 --> 00:08:01,360
Since things worked out like this,
I'll keep trying.

111
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,031
I mean it.

112
00:08:06,041 --> 00:08:09,728
No, this is more than enough.

113
00:08:12,302 --> 00:08:16,062
Don't get yourself hit over
something that won't work out.

114
00:08:18,007 --> 00:08:19,519
I'll get going.

115
00:08:35,845 --> 00:08:38,214
- This is Strategic Planning.
- This is Strategic Planning.

116
00:08:38,214 --> 00:08:39,322
There will be an announcement.

117
00:08:39,322 --> 00:08:41,501
Please wait for
the official announcement.

118
00:08:41,501 --> 00:08:43,424
Our department doesn't handle that.

119
00:08:43,424 --> 00:08:46,316
Yes, I'm sorry.

120
00:08:48,731 --> 00:08:51,644
I'm sorry I couldn't put a stop to it.

121
00:08:51,644 --> 00:08:54,774
Wasn't it your job before to
keep an eye on that second son?

122
00:08:54,774 --> 00:08:59,332
That guy came and
caused a scene at your event.

123
00:08:59,332 --> 00:09:01,654
Does it make sense
that you didn't know about it?

124
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:07,104
Hey, do you know how much money
we spent on this project?

125
00:09:07,104 --> 00:09:11,803
Yet, no one is interested
in the new food item.

126
00:09:11,803 --> 00:09:13,714
Everyone is asking about
the cleaners instead.

127
00:09:13,714 --> 00:09:18,142
What are you going to do?
What are you going to about it!

128
00:09:18,142 --> 00:09:19,421
I'm sorry.

129
00:09:19,421 --> 00:09:21,868
Is "sorry" going to cut it?

130
00:09:21,868 --> 00:09:23,047
Oh.

131
00:09:24,198 --> 00:09:25,657
Yes.

132
00:09:26,356 --> 00:09:30,124
We are not responsible for the cleaners.

133
00:09:30,124 --> 00:09:34,037
Nothing's been confirmed, so please
wait for an official announcement.

134
00:09:34,037 --> 00:09:35,413
Yes.

135
00:09:38,038 --> 00:09:39,951
Move!

136
00:09:46,221 --> 00:09:48,028
Are you all crazy?

137
00:09:48,028 --> 00:09:51,163
What were you thinking going up there?

138
00:09:51,163 --> 00:09:54,510
You trusted in the CEO's son
and caused that scene?

139
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:58,758
I could lose my job
because of you people!

140
00:09:58,758 --> 00:10:01,649
Hey, stop thinking so negatively.

141
00:10:01,649 --> 00:10:03,078
He is the CEO's son.

142
00:10:03,078 --> 00:10:04,158
You never know.

143
00:10:04,158 --> 00:10:06,472
CEO Byun might do everything
that his son asked for.

144
00:10:06,472 --> 00:10:09,703
- That is true.
- He might.

145
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:15,941
Oh, what's wrong?

146
00:10:15,941 --> 00:10:17,951
Did someone hit you?

147
00:10:18,451 --> 00:10:23,019
Do what his son asked for?
Yeah, right.

148
00:10:23,019 --> 00:10:25,866
It's all over. It's over.

149
00:10:28,652 --> 00:10:30,495
So annoying.

150
00:10:30,495 --> 00:10:32,020
To his own son!

151
00:10:45,693 --> 00:10:51,804
Even if he's angry,
how could he do this to his son?

152
00:10:51,804 --> 00:10:54,806
I guess it was a part of the process.

153
00:10:54,806 --> 00:10:56,596
I tried doing what I could.

154
00:10:56,596 --> 00:10:59,056
I'm sorry things worked out this way.

155
00:10:59,056 --> 00:11:03,121
Why would you be sorry? We're fine.

156
00:11:03,121 --> 00:11:09,773
Telling all those people that
we are important was more than enough.

157
00:11:09,773 --> 00:11:12,942
Yeah, you were cool.

158
00:11:12,942 --> 00:11:14,481
Thank you.

159
00:11:14,481 --> 00:11:16,761
Where did Joon go, anyway?

160
00:11:16,761 --> 00:11:18,923
She followed you to the CEO's office.

161
00:11:18,923 --> 00:11:20,731
Didn't you see her?

162
00:11:24,364 --> 00:11:26,296
Eat this.

163
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:29,735
- You eat one too, Honey.
- Okay.

164
00:11:29,735 --> 00:11:31,256
Here you go.

165
00:11:31,256 --> 00:11:34,503
Yum. It's sweet.

166
00:11:34,503 --> 00:11:39,193
Oh, it's winter already.

167
00:11:39,193 --> 00:11:40,966
Every day, it's colder.

168
00:11:40,966 --> 00:11:42,309
- Good, right?
- Yes.

169
00:11:42,309 --> 00:11:43,716
Is it good?

170
00:11:45,201 --> 00:11:46,503
Here.

171
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:16,149
I'm here, Dad.

172
00:12:17,243 --> 00:12:19,783
Sorry it's been so long.

173
00:12:21,683 --> 00:12:23,668
<i>You're a coward.</i>

174
00:12:24,677 --> 00:12:27,828
You're scared and running
before even starting.

175
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:38,164
You have lots of excuses,
and you haven't even tried.

176
00:12:38,164 --> 00:12:40,241
Coward.

177
00:12:41,433 --> 00:12:43,493
Am I really?

178
00:12:46,922 --> 00:12:52,254
Am I really... a coward?

179
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:38,740
Jae Hoon.

180
00:13:44,817 --> 00:13:47,269
Joon's not home yet.

181
00:13:48,461 --> 00:13:51,621
Why are you like that?

182
00:13:51,621 --> 00:13:53,971
You only think about yourself, don't you?

183
00:13:53,971 --> 00:13:58,322
You don't care if others get hurt
or have a hard time because of you.

184
00:13:58,322 --> 00:14:00,912
Only your life matters to you.

185
00:14:00,912 --> 00:14:03,182
I'm really sorry, Jae Hoon.

186
00:14:03,182 --> 00:14:07,173
I didn't mean to ruin the event.

187
00:14:07,173 --> 00:14:13,660
It was really important
to the cleaning employees.

188
00:14:13,660 --> 00:14:15,567
Cleaning employees?

189
00:14:15,567 --> 00:14:18,339
Since when did you care
about people like that?

190
00:14:18,339 --> 00:14:19,403
Jae Hoon.

191
00:14:19,403 --> 00:14:21,916
If you're going to cause problems...

192
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:23,870
do it outside the company.

193
00:14:23,870 --> 00:14:26,765
Don't cause a headache
for so many people.

194
00:14:27,748 --> 00:14:31,870
I'm getting really tired of you.

195
00:14:39,937 --> 00:14:41,714
<i>About Hyuk...</i>

196
00:14:42,416 --> 00:14:44,966
What do you think of him?

197
00:14:44,966 --> 00:14:47,363
I don't know much,
but he sure has a lot of spirit.

198
00:14:47,363 --> 00:14:48,797
Yeah?

199
00:14:49,772 --> 00:14:52,100
You think so too, right?

200
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:54,020
That kid...

201
00:14:54,020 --> 00:14:57,248
I wondered what he would be able to do.

202
00:14:57,248 --> 00:15:01,938
He has a more ambitious spirit
than I thought.

203
00:15:04,706 --> 00:15:07,869
While we're on the topic...

204
00:15:07,869 --> 00:15:12,453
why don't you take him into your
Strategic Planning team?

205
00:15:12,947 --> 00:15:15,466
See if he can make it or not.

206
00:15:15,466 --> 00:15:19,539
Take him in and put him to work.

207
00:15:21,451 --> 00:15:24,764
I can't do that, CEO Byun.

208
00:15:24,764 --> 00:15:26,464
You can't?

209
00:15:27,967 --> 00:15:29,032
Why not?

210
00:15:29,032 --> 00:15:33,317
If you want him on my team,
do it officially.

211
00:15:33,317 --> 00:15:38,078
As it turns out,
we're hiring new interns.

212
00:15:38,078 --> 00:15:43,128
Getting hired fairly
by his own merits into Gangsu

213
00:15:43,128 --> 00:15:46,408
is what's best for you and Hyuk.

214
00:15:46,408 --> 00:15:48,423
Oh, no.

215
00:15:48,423 --> 00:15:51,782
He couldn't even graduate
college in the US.

216
00:15:51,782 --> 00:15:55,551
He's only a high school graduate
and has no experience.

217
00:15:55,551 --> 00:16:00,365
How can he get hired by our company?

218
00:16:01,091 --> 00:16:04,902
We won't be looking at academics,
gender, or age this time.

219
00:16:04,902 --> 00:16:07,865
We won't be looking at the
resume they've built up.

220
00:16:07,865 --> 00:16:12,871
We'll be choosing based on
their capabilities and character.

221
00:16:12,871 --> 00:16:14,864
So...

222
00:16:14,864 --> 00:16:17,833
you're saying Hyuk can get in?

223
00:16:17,833 --> 00:16:20,971
You're curious to know
if he can make it or not.

224
00:16:20,971 --> 00:16:25,293
If he can make it,
he should get in.

225
00:16:47,264 --> 00:16:51,217
<i>The intern applications start today.
Don't be stubborn.</i>

226
00:17:03,441 --> 00:17:06,152
Is it true that you won't be
looking at the resume?

227
00:17:06,152 --> 00:17:10,292
- Yes.
- Oh, Gangsu Group's doing good work.

228
00:17:10,292 --> 00:17:12,301
Go on.

229
00:17:14,137 --> 00:17:16,914
What? You want me to what?

230
00:17:16,914 --> 00:17:20,654
Apply for the open call for interns.

231
00:17:21,201 --> 00:17:25,661
If you pass everything
and become an intern

232
00:17:25,661 --> 00:17:29,162
I'll think about hiring
the cleaning staff directly.

233
00:17:29,162 --> 00:17:33,356
Apply today if you want to be
held responsible for your words.

234
00:17:33,356 --> 00:17:36,801
Father, this isn't right.

235
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:39,973
- Why not?
- An intern?

236
00:17:41,964 --> 00:17:46,137
How could I get in?
You know my education and resume.

237
00:17:46,137 --> 00:17:47,691
This isn't a proper negotiation.

238
00:17:47,691 --> 00:17:50,781
You're basically saying you won't do it.

239
00:17:50,781 --> 00:17:53,432
A person who makes claims
without even knowing a thing.

240
00:17:53,432 --> 00:17:55,942
Is that a proper negotiation?

241
00:17:55,942 --> 00:17:58,343
- Father.
- I'm done talking.

242
00:17:58,343 --> 00:18:02,568
It's up to you if you
want to accept it or not.

243
00:18:19,117 --> 00:18:20,653
Hello?

244
00:18:22,914 --> 00:18:25,419
Wh... what? Intern?

245
00:18:26,852 --> 00:18:29,193
Who? You?

246
00:18:29,193 --> 00:18:31,055
Yes, me.

247
00:18:31,055 --> 00:18:32,786
Does this make sense?

248
00:18:32,786 --> 00:18:34,893
He wants me to apply to be an intern.

249
00:18:34,893 --> 00:18:39,334
He says I need to pass so he'll
consider hiring the cleaners.

250
00:18:39,334 --> 00:18:41,273
What do you think this means?

251
00:18:41,273 --> 00:18:45,019
What else? He's saying screw off.

252
00:18:45,942 --> 00:18:49,349
Well, there's no need
to say it so directly.

253
00:18:49,349 --> 00:18:50,721
Your education is lacking.

254
00:18:50,721 --> 00:18:55,076
All you have going for you
is that you're the CEO's son.

255
00:18:55,076 --> 00:18:57,535
It's not like the CEO
is giving you the position.

256
00:18:57,535 --> 00:19:00,579
He wants you to fight fairly
with others and pass on your own.

257
00:19:00,579 --> 00:19:02,259
Yes.

258
00:19:02,259 --> 00:19:04,574
He must be telling me to screw off.

259
00:19:04,574 --> 00:19:06,689
I heard they're not looking at
the resume this time.

260
00:19:06,689 --> 00:19:09,307
Even so, there's a limit to it.

261
00:19:09,307 --> 00:19:12,938
At the final stages, what would
they look at if not the resume?

262
00:19:12,938 --> 00:19:14,127
Hold on.

263
00:19:14,127 --> 00:19:20,723
So, this whole thing about "no resumes"
was all about the company's image?

264
00:19:20,723 --> 00:19:23,026
Yet, you were pushing me to apply?

265
00:19:23,026 --> 00:19:24,683
Even though you knew it was all a lie.

266
00:19:24,683 --> 00:19:27,035
Joon, you're going to
apply to be an intern too?

267
00:19:27,035 --> 00:19:29,035
Don't be ridiculous.

268
00:19:29,035 --> 00:19:32,403
You and Hyuk are on a different level.

269
00:19:32,403 --> 00:19:36,394
Yes, Joon is on a different level
of intelligence than me.

270
00:19:36,394 --> 00:19:37,644
I'm glad that you know.

271
00:19:37,644 --> 00:19:39,664
There's no need for you
to be conflicted.

272
00:19:39,664 --> 00:19:41,844
You will fail that intern interview.

273
00:19:41,844 --> 00:19:44,384
Gangsu Group will re-sign
with the cleaning contractors.

274
00:19:44,384 --> 00:19:49,517
Then CEO Min will continue
to reap the benefits.

275
00:19:49,517 --> 00:19:52,384
Well, then there's
nothing to think about.

276
00:19:52,384 --> 00:19:53,925
Just apply.

277
00:19:53,925 --> 00:19:55,959
Yes, right?

278
00:19:55,959 --> 00:19:57,294
What?

279
00:19:57,294 --> 00:19:58,753
- Do what?
- Hey, Baek Joon.

280
00:19:58,753 --> 00:20:00,929
You said you'd get them hired.

281
00:20:00,929 --> 00:20:03,196
Their lives are in your hands right now.

282
00:20:03,196 --> 00:20:04,867
You're quitting without even trying?

283
00:20:04,867 --> 00:20:06,730
No, that's not it.

284
00:20:06,730 --> 00:20:08,959
Don't egg him on to do things
he can't be responsible for.

285
00:20:08,959 --> 00:20:13,398
Then you shouldn't have done that
performance at the event at all, Hyuk.

286
00:20:13,398 --> 00:20:14,874
That is true.

287
00:20:14,874 --> 00:20:17,943
No. Don't even think about it.
You can't do it.

288
00:20:17,943 --> 00:20:19,469
Yes, I can't.

289
00:20:19,469 --> 00:20:22,155
A man is giving up before trying?

290
00:20:22,155 --> 00:20:24,540
Yes, that's not right.

291
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:26,538
I told you not to do it.

292
00:20:26,538 --> 00:20:29,142
I told you to do it.

293
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:44,567
Your father told Hyuk
to apply for an internship?

294
00:20:44,567 --> 00:20:46,064
I know, right?

295
00:20:46,064 --> 00:20:49,263
Even if he is angry,
why would he tell Hyuk to intern?

296
00:20:49,263 --> 00:20:50,957
It's a bit too much.

297
00:20:51,634 --> 00:20:53,971
What in the world is he thinking?

298
00:20:56,069 --> 00:20:58,772
Is there anything you know, Mother?

299
00:20:58,772 --> 00:21:00,334
<i>You told me to give him wings.</i>

300
00:21:00,334 --> 00:21:02,680
<i>What do you mean by that?</i>

301
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:05,824
If he has wings, he'll fly.

302
00:21:05,824 --> 00:21:08,003
I don't know if he's a phoenix.

303
00:21:08,003 --> 00:21:13,479
I need to throw him to know
if he's an eagle or a baby chick.

304
00:21:15,413 --> 00:21:17,343
Father said that?

305
00:21:17,343 --> 00:21:22,186
I wondered what that meant, at the time.

306
00:21:23,144 --> 00:21:24,493
Hey, Woo Sung.

307
00:21:24,493 --> 00:21:29,131
Do you think your father is trying
to help train Hyuk right now?

308
00:21:29,772 --> 00:21:33,888
Shouldn't you help Hyuk
as his older brother, then?

309
00:21:33,888 --> 00:21:35,776
Come on, Mother.

310
00:21:35,776 --> 00:21:38,224
You know he's just a troublemaker.

311
00:21:38,224 --> 00:21:40,044
How could I help?

312
00:21:40,044 --> 00:21:43,897
Hey, Hyuk didn't turn
his back on you back then.

313
00:21:43,897 --> 00:21:47,176
That young thing was
protecting his older brother...

314
00:21:50,765 --> 00:21:54,240
Never mind. Let's not talk about it.

315
00:22:01,037 --> 00:22:03,486
Oh, I can't do it. I can't.

316
00:22:03,486 --> 00:22:07,203
How can I do it?
Even if they're not looking at resumes.

317
00:22:07,203 --> 00:22:09,555
I need to know something
to pass the tests.

318
00:22:09,555 --> 00:22:12,105
Oh, I can't do it. I can't do it.

319
00:22:28,042 --> 00:22:31,862
Is Hyuk that poorly educated?

320
00:22:31,862 --> 00:22:34,662
I don't really know.

321
00:22:34,662 --> 00:22:37,608
How much of a bad student was he?

322
00:22:37,608 --> 00:22:39,421
It can't be just that.

323
00:22:39,421 --> 00:22:42,429
Yeah, it can't just be about that.

324
00:22:42,429 --> 00:22:44,654
What would happen if he doesn't pass?

325
00:22:44,654 --> 00:22:48,222
That determines whether
we become direct hires or not.

326
00:22:48,222 --> 00:22:51,894
It must be such
an emotional burden, right?

327
00:22:51,894 --> 00:22:53,692
Yeah, yeah.

328
00:23:20,635 --> 00:23:22,634
What brings you by?

329
00:23:22,634 --> 00:23:26,413
I was just curious about where you lived.

330
00:23:26,994 --> 00:23:29,715
It's not as bad as I thought it'd be.

331
00:23:29,715 --> 00:23:31,355
My home is very shabby.

332
00:23:31,355 --> 00:23:33,275
Would you like to go to a cafe nearby?

333
00:23:33,275 --> 00:23:34,964
It's okay, Jae Hoon.

334
00:23:34,964 --> 00:23:37,105
Don't worry about that.

335
00:23:37,105 --> 00:23:40,365
There's a cafe five minutes away.

336
00:23:40,365 --> 00:23:43,217
He says he was curious
about where I lived.

337
00:23:44,012 --> 00:23:46,286
Then I should show him.

338
00:23:49,484 --> 00:23:51,230
Come on, Brother.

339
00:23:58,393 --> 00:24:00,586
Wait here.

340
00:24:36,411 --> 00:24:38,086
Are you okay with coffee, Woo Sung?

341
00:24:38,086 --> 00:24:41,861
No, I don't drink coffee after 6:00 p.m.

342
00:24:42,506 --> 00:24:44,844
Then I'll drink alone.

343
00:24:47,656 --> 00:24:50,835
Ah, okay. I'm recharged.

344
00:24:50,835 --> 00:24:53,259
It’s a bit small, right?

345
00:24:53,259 --> 00:24:56,369
Sit wherever you feel comfortable.

346
00:25:01,635 --> 00:25:04,527
So, Father told you
to apply for the internship.

347
00:25:04,527 --> 00:25:05,844
That's what I heard.

348
00:25:05,844 --> 00:25:07,396
Yes.

349
00:25:15,384 --> 00:25:16,842
What is it?

350
00:25:17,935 --> 00:25:20,432
You said you needed money.

351
00:25:20,432 --> 00:25:22,965
I gave you more than enough in there.

352
00:25:22,965 --> 00:25:25,207
Take it and leave Korea for a while.

353
00:25:25,207 --> 00:25:29,548
Go on vacation
and give your mind a break.

354
00:25:29,548 --> 00:25:35,102
Also, don't take Father's offer
too seriously.

355
00:25:36,436 --> 00:25:38,595
Don't act up, kid.

356
00:25:39,978 --> 00:25:42,968
You wouldn't even
pass the intern interview.

357
00:25:42,968 --> 00:25:46,406
What are you rambling on about
direct hiring of cleaners?

358
00:25:47,137 --> 00:25:51,696
Just shut your mouth and live quietly.

359
00:25:53,517 --> 00:25:55,545
That's what he means by it.

360
00:26:04,332 --> 00:26:05,893
Hyuk.

361
00:26:08,154 --> 00:26:10,166
You've done enough.

362
00:26:10,166 --> 00:26:13,273
You've shown your presence enough.

363
00:26:14,829 --> 00:26:19,351
Stop now and go have fun
somewhere outside of this country.

364
00:26:19,351 --> 00:26:23,721
I'll give you whatever you need
while you're there, okay?

365
00:26:29,079 --> 00:26:30,960
<i>Please, Hyuk.</i>

366
00:26:31,651 --> 00:26:35,154
I'll do whatever you need.

367
00:26:35,730 --> 00:26:37,771
Save me just this once.

368
00:26:37,771 --> 00:26:41,277
You know I'll die if our father knows.

369
00:26:41,277 --> 00:26:43,963
You're the only person who can help me.

370
00:26:43,963 --> 00:26:46,500
You're the only one...

371
00:26:48,369 --> 00:26:51,978
I'll do anything you want, okay?

372
00:26:54,471 --> 00:26:58,594
So, Hyuk. Save me this once.

373
00:26:59,228 --> 00:27:01,074
I'm begging like this.

374
00:27:05,607 --> 00:27:09,042
My goodness. I can't believe this.

375
00:27:09,042 --> 00:27:10,912
You little bastard.

376
00:27:10,912 --> 00:27:12,596
Honey!

377
00:27:12,596 --> 00:27:14,955
Have you no fear?

378
00:27:14,955 --> 00:27:19,308
You took the car out tonight
and hit a person?

379
00:27:20,502 --> 00:27:22,690
What? What happened?

380
00:27:25,146 --> 00:27:27,501
Hyuk... Hyuk.

381
00:27:28,922 --> 00:27:30,270
I'm sorry.

382
00:27:30,270 --> 00:27:32,076
Turn yourself in!

383
00:27:32,441 --> 00:27:36,257
Take responsibility
for the things you've done!

384
00:27:37,441 --> 00:27:41,310
Honey, please. Our Hyuk is still young.

385
00:27:41,310 --> 00:27:45,340
He still has his future.
Please help him this once.

386
00:27:45,340 --> 00:27:47,557
I don't know.

387
00:27:49,096 --> 00:27:51,143
Honey!

388
00:27:51,143 --> 00:27:54,342
Honey, Honey!

389
00:27:54,342 --> 00:27:56,126
Honey!

390
00:28:13,101 --> 00:28:14,969
This is amusing.

391
00:28:17,076 --> 00:28:19,838
When you say you'll do anything for me...

392
00:28:22,388 --> 00:28:24,931
it means you're desperate.

393
00:28:25,676 --> 00:28:27,113
Right?

394
00:28:32,097 --> 00:28:34,779
Now that I think about it...

395
00:28:36,382 --> 00:28:38,977
there was only one thing
you could do for me.

396
00:28:38,977 --> 00:28:42,597
Ah, I'm not upset by it though.

397
00:28:45,592 --> 00:28:48,002
For one thing, it's not fun anymore.

398
00:28:49,342 --> 00:28:54,189
Whatever it is...
people doing things for me.

399
00:28:57,037 --> 00:29:01,755
You're not saying you're really going
to apply for this internship, are you?

400
00:29:06,082 --> 00:29:09,340
Honestly, I wasn't up for the task.

401
00:29:09,340 --> 00:29:13,303
But you showed up here
worrying about me.

402
00:29:13,303 --> 00:29:17,805
I feel pathetic at the fact
that I was scared.

403
00:29:18,413 --> 00:29:20,405
So, you're doing it?

404
00:29:20,952 --> 00:29:23,625
You'll cheer me on, right, Brother?

405
00:29:53,788 --> 00:29:58,000
Tell him he doesn't need
to feel too burdened by us.

406
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,598
Everyone has to make his own living.

407
00:29:59,598 --> 00:30:02,020
People have to live their own lives.

408
00:30:02,020 --> 00:30:05,816
Of course, he doesn't need
to feel responsible for us at all.

409
00:30:05,816 --> 00:30:07,243
That's right.

410
00:30:19,836 --> 00:30:21,888
Are you just leaving like that?

411
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:25,049
What is he thinking?

412
00:30:25,049 --> 00:30:26,585
Do you know anything?

413
00:30:26,585 --> 00:30:29,311
Thinking? Nothing, really.

414
00:30:29,311 --> 00:30:32,519
I just got mad on my own
and got upset.

415
00:30:33,569 --> 00:30:35,979
Is that really it?

416
00:30:35,979 --> 00:30:37,336
Hm?

417
00:30:37,336 --> 00:30:38,832
I'm sure that's all it is.

418
00:30:38,832 --> 00:30:43,539
He probably only said it out of
embarrassment in front of his brother.

419
00:30:44,284 --> 00:30:47,451
- Don't worry. I'll take care of it.
- No.

420
00:30:47,451 --> 00:30:49,376
Don't do a single thing.

421
00:30:50,063 --> 00:30:53,192
Let him go for the internship.

422
00:30:53,192 --> 00:30:58,021
He needs to see how low and
how much of a nobody he is.

423
00:30:58,021 --> 00:30:59,946
He needs to get out there to see.

424
00:31:15,461 --> 00:31:17,760
Joon, what did you just say?

425
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:20,046
Let's do it together, that intern test.

426
00:31:20,046 --> 00:31:22,386
Really? You too?

427
00:31:24,070 --> 00:31:25,497
Why, suddenly?

428
00:31:25,497 --> 00:31:28,714
I can't leave you
to get screwed by yourself.

429
00:31:28,714 --> 00:31:29,778
Joon.

430
00:31:29,778 --> 00:31:32,171
Of course, it's not free,
so don't expect too much.

431
00:31:32,171 --> 00:31:34,378
Intern tests all have three rounds.

432
00:31:34,378 --> 00:31:36,821
First round, human resources
screening test.

433
00:31:36,821 --> 00:31:38,579
Second round, a practical skills test.

434
00:31:38,579 --> 00:31:40,141
Third round, a personal interview.

435
00:31:40,141 --> 00:31:42,670
For every round you pass,
200,000 won and you get special training.

436
00:31:42,670 --> 00:31:46,039
If you pass the whole thing,
I get a bonus of 100,000 on top.

437
00:31:46,039 --> 00:31:48,556
How about it?

438
00:31:48,556 --> 00:31:51,250
That doesn't matter to me.

439
00:31:52,095 --> 00:31:54,806
Special training though? What's that?

440
00:31:54,806 --> 00:31:57,387
They won't accept just anyone,
even if they don't look at resumes.

441
00:31:57,387 --> 00:32:00,855
That means they need
other means to evaluate you.

442
00:32:00,855 --> 00:32:02,304
Language.

443
00:32:03,289 --> 00:32:04,890
Math.

444
00:32:04,890 --> 00:32:06,037
Deduction.

445
00:32:06,613 --> 00:32:09,964
Spatial perception, current events.

446
00:32:10,828 --> 00:32:13,143
You need master all of these things.

447
00:32:13,143 --> 00:32:14,397
All of this?

448
00:32:14,397 --> 00:32:16,105
Yes.

449
00:32:16,105 --> 00:32:20,715
Last of all... this one too.

450
00:32:23,263 --> 00:32:24,885
<i>[Human Management]</i>

451
00:32:33,647 --> 00:32:37,269
<i>[Interning is my path to survival!]</i>

452
00:32:43,814 --> 00:32:45,696
You think that will work?

453
00:32:51,799 --> 00:32:54,163
You agree, right?

454
00:33:02,083 --> 00:33:03,515
<i>Hey, Byun Hyuk.</i>

455
00:33:04,067 --> 00:33:05,906
You're not studying, are you?

456
00:33:05,906 --> 00:33:07,623
Get back to studying now!

457
00:33:07,623 --> 00:33:10,311
Oh, oh. Okay, I will.

458
00:33:10,311 --> 00:33:13,230
I'll study. I will.

459
00:33:13,230 --> 00:33:15,498
Joon knows me so well.

460
00:33:53,390 --> 00:33:54,992
Eat while you study.

461
00:33:57,595 --> 00:33:59,451
Yum, this rice.

462
00:33:59,451 --> 00:34:01,535
It's so good.

463
00:34:02,173 --> 00:34:04,837
The ramen noodles are really great.

464
00:34:19,538 --> 00:34:23,378
These are the questions they've used
in the past three years.

465
00:34:23,378 --> 00:34:25,755
It's a study guide of past exams.

466
00:34:25,755 --> 00:34:28,398
It was very hard to get this.

467
00:34:28,398 --> 00:34:29,565
Use this to study.

468
00:34:29,565 --> 00:34:31,394
We'll make good use of it, Madam Ahn.

469
00:34:31,394 --> 00:34:32,797
Here.

470
00:34:32,797 --> 00:34:36,447
It's a study guide that Madam Ahn
worked hard to get, so memorize it.

471
00:34:37,306 --> 00:34:40,740
There's so much I have to memorize, Joon.

472
00:34:45,068 --> 00:34:47,550
Ah... yum.

473
00:34:48,771 --> 00:34:50,958
- Keep it up.
- Okay.

474
00:35:23,385 --> 00:35:28,262
I managed to get
these documents from the company.

475
00:35:34,527 --> 00:35:35,793
Thank you, Mister.

476
00:35:35,793 --> 00:35:37,659
No need to thank me.

477
00:35:40,588 --> 00:35:42,876
Oh, you're resting.

478
00:36:37,878 --> 00:36:39,596
Is it going well?

479
00:36:41,452 --> 00:36:43,077
I don't know.

480
00:36:43,831 --> 00:36:47,782
I'm just doing what Joon tells me to.

481
00:36:47,782 --> 00:36:50,385
It's so hard, my friend.

482
00:36:53,929 --> 00:36:58,416
I've been pooping blood.

483
00:37:01,755 --> 00:37:03,719
<i>Why are you pushing so hard?</i>

484
00:37:03,719 --> 00:37:06,697
No matter how much you rile him up,
Hyuk won't make it.

485
00:37:06,697 --> 00:37:07,871
He won't pass.

486
00:37:07,871 --> 00:37:11,780
Even if he passes rounds one and two,
he won't make it past round three.

487
00:37:11,780 --> 00:37:13,291
Why?

488
00:37:16,755 --> 00:37:18,880
Chief Byun Woo Sung will fail him.

489
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:23,510
Why does he go that far
to keep Hyuk in check?

490
00:37:24,233 --> 00:37:27,443
He's not keeping him in check.
He looks down on him.

491
00:37:27,443 --> 00:37:29,492
A younger brother is giving it a try.

492
00:37:29,492 --> 00:37:31,673
The older brother
purposely gets in the way.

493
00:37:31,673 --> 00:37:33,454
Is that merely looking down on him?

494
00:37:33,454 --> 00:37:34,835
I think differently.

495
00:37:34,835 --> 00:37:38,358
Are you getting involved in
Hyuk's sibling fights too?

496
00:37:38,358 --> 00:37:42,193
You could even end up being in charge
of taking care of Hyuk instead of me.

497
00:37:42,193 --> 00:37:44,273
What? Can't I do that?

498
00:37:44,273 --> 00:37:47,384
You do it, so why can't I do it?

499
00:37:47,384 --> 00:37:50,074
Are you serious about that nonsense?

500
00:37:50,074 --> 00:37:52,835
You said you've been friends
with Hyuk since kindergarten.

501
00:37:52,835 --> 00:37:55,235
Don't you know Hyuk at all?

502
00:37:55,235 --> 00:37:58,099
Then what about you?
What do you know about him?

503
00:37:58,099 --> 00:37:59,739
You haven't known him that long.

504
00:37:59,739 --> 00:38:03,940
At least, I know the burden of
responsibility he's carrying.

505
00:38:03,940 --> 00:38:08,311
Do you think Hyuk knows what
the word "responsibility" means?

506
00:38:08,311 --> 00:38:10,380
If he didn't know,
why would he be doing this?

507
00:38:10,380 --> 00:38:11,862
He could live life in comfort.

508
00:38:11,862 --> 00:38:14,644
Do you really not know?
It's all because of you.

509
00:38:14,644 --> 00:38:18,065
Because you keep telling him to do it
and encouraging him.

510
00:38:18,065 --> 00:38:22,889
He doesn't even know what he's doing
and he's running in head first.

511
00:38:25,175 --> 00:38:28,869
What if it is because of me?
Is that wrong?

512
00:38:31,606 --> 00:38:34,894
What do you mean by that?

513
00:38:34,894 --> 00:38:38,527
Whatever the reason,
he's doing something with sincerity.

514
00:38:38,527 --> 00:38:40,527
Isn't that good enough?

515
00:38:42,494 --> 00:38:44,557
<i>What is it?</i>

516
00:38:44,557 --> 00:38:46,916
That burden of responsibility?

517
00:38:54,106 --> 00:38:56,795
Hey, Byun Hyuk. Are you sleeping?

518
00:39:31,420 --> 00:39:32,472
<i>[Mister Lee]</i>

