00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:53,057
Good luck in there!

573
00:43:53,057 --> 00:43:55,407
Good luck!

574
00:43:56,639 --> 00:43:59,293
Pass, pass, pass!

575
00:44:02,271 --> 00:44:04,193
Yes, Madam.

576
00:44:04,193 --> 00:44:07,862
Young Master Hyuk has
safely arrived at the company.

577
00:44:07,862 --> 00:44:10,112
Really?

578
00:44:10,112 --> 00:44:12,603
He wasn't late, was he?

579
00:44:14,416 --> 00:44:16,177
All right.

580
00:44:59,273 --> 00:45:01,755
You don't need to be scared or nervous.

581
00:45:01,755 --> 00:45:04,317
Practice like a battle
and battle like practice.

582
00:45:04,317 --> 00:45:06,788
Don't worry. I'll be there with you.

583
00:45:06,788 --> 00:45:07,992
Got it?

584
00:45:09,195 --> 00:45:12,686
<i>Yes, Joon is with me.</i>

585
00:45:12,686 --> 00:45:15,451
<i>I have the study guide from Madam Ahn.</i>

586
00:45:15,451 --> 00:45:17,400
Good luck!

587
00:45:17,400 --> 00:45:20,813
<i>I have the information from Mister Lee.</i>

588
00:45:25,731 --> 00:45:28,271
<i>I'm not alone in this test.</i>

589
00:45:38,159 --> 00:45:41,364
<i>I'm starting to see the questions.</i>

590
00:45:41,364 --> 00:45:44,304
<i>Huh? I can see the answers too.</i>

591
00:45:44,304 --> 00:45:46,155
<i>Wow. Awesome.</i>

592
00:45:46,155 --> 00:45:48,414
<i>Oh, oh. This one!</i>

593
00:45:48,414 --> 00:45:50,318
<i>I know this one.</i>

594
00:46:01,405 --> 00:46:03,505
Chief, Chief!

595
00:46:05,331 --> 00:46:06,512
What is it?

596
00:46:06,512 --> 00:46:08,965
There's a disaster.

597
00:46:08,965 --> 00:46:14,907
They say that Byun Hyuk
has passed the first round test.

598
00:46:26,112 --> 00:46:28,945
Wow, this is great.

599
00:46:28,945 --> 00:46:31,960
No need to be so happy.
It's only the first round.

600
00:46:31,960 --> 00:46:34,898
The first round is not so easy.

601
00:46:35,485 --> 00:46:39,065
Wait, what happens after first round?

602
00:46:39,065 --> 00:46:42,322
What else?
He takes the second round test.

603
00:46:42,322 --> 00:46:44,568
What is the second round test?

604
00:46:44,568 --> 00:46:47,771
The second round test is a blind test.

605
00:46:47,771 --> 00:46:52,199
You need to find the Gangsu Food product
from the products in front of you.

606
00:46:52,199 --> 00:46:56,409
Carefully taste the food in front of you
and write your answer on the sheet.

607
00:46:56,409 --> 00:46:59,735
Okay, let's get started then.

608
00:47:35,864 --> 00:47:37,514
Eat while you study.

609
00:47:52,356 --> 00:47:55,626
Yum, Gangsu.

610
00:48:01,563 --> 00:48:02,867
<i>Yum, hot bar.</i>

611
00:48:02,867 --> 00:48:04,673
<i>Don't forget it.</i>

612
00:48:04,673 --> 00:48:06,434
<i>I'm going to test you on it.</i>

613
00:48:11,429 --> 00:48:15,286
<i>In the 18th century,
he started the realist movement.</i>

614
00:48:15,286 --> 00:48:17,708
<i>A realist and reformist?</i>

615
00:48:17,708 --> 00:48:19,460
Ha Nam Hee.

616
00:48:19,460 --> 00:48:22,514
A realist and reformist?

617
00:48:22,514 --> 00:48:24,362
Post Joseon era, it's Oh Seon Jong.

618
00:48:24,362 --> 00:48:25,688
Yes.

619
00:49:05,173 --> 00:49:07,394
Yum.

620
00:49:08,083 --> 00:49:09,492
Yes, yes.

621
00:49:10,190 --> 00:49:11,902
This is the taste.

622
00:49:21,822 --> 00:49:23,836
Yeah!

623
00:49:25,550 --> 00:49:27,605
No, Joon.

624
00:49:27,605 --> 00:49:29,548
Just one second, no five seconds.

625
00:49:29,548 --> 00:49:30,833
People are watching.

626
00:49:30,833 --> 00:49:33,677
Three, four, five.

627
00:49:33,677 --> 00:49:34,759
I did well, right?

628
00:49:34,759 --> 00:49:36,230
You did. That was great.

629
00:49:36,230 --> 00:49:39,032
I really didn't think
a hot bar would be there.

630
00:49:39,032 --> 00:49:40,804
The cup ramen confused me a little.

631
00:49:40,804 --> 00:49:44,615
- D, D, D, D!
- D, D, D, D!

632
00:49:44,615 --> 00:49:47,425
Let's go to round three now.

633
00:49:47,425 --> 00:49:49,199
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

634
00:49:49,199 --> 00:49:51,088
Good job.

635
00:49:51,088 --> 00:49:54,898
What? My Hyuk passed round two?

636
00:49:54,898 --> 00:49:58,076
Really? He even passed round two?

637
00:49:58,869 --> 00:50:03,219
May I ask you one more question?

638
00:50:03,219 --> 00:50:07,398
Did a girl named Baek Joon pass too?

639
00:50:08,639 --> 00:50:11,528
Ah, I see.

640
00:50:12,445 --> 00:50:16,027
All right. Thank you, Secretary Park.

641
00:50:17,170 --> 00:50:19,840
Baek Joon? Who's that?

642
00:50:19,840 --> 00:50:21,710
You don't need to know.

643
00:50:23,159 --> 00:50:25,253
What's going on?

644
00:50:26,050 --> 00:50:28,768
Is she really Pyunggang?

645
00:50:30,224 --> 00:50:32,402
Really? Yes.

646
00:50:32,402 --> 00:50:36,001
So, Hyuk even passed round two?

647
00:50:36,001 --> 00:50:39,572
So, you had a good idea,
Managing Director Seol.

648
00:50:44,233 --> 00:50:46,063
Well, then...

649
00:50:46,063 --> 00:50:50,001
Who's going into the final interview?

650
00:51:24,132 --> 00:51:26,945
Tell us your positive traits.

651
00:51:26,945 --> 00:51:30,726
My positive traits?

652
00:51:30,726 --> 00:51:33,240
An abundance of sensitivity.

653
00:51:34,594 --> 00:51:36,777
I happen to like poems a lot.

654
00:51:36,777 --> 00:51:39,777
I have over 100 poems memorized.

655
00:51:39,777 --> 00:51:42,443
Should I recite one?

656
00:51:44,092 --> 00:51:46,324
"When looking at me
disgusts you and you leave"--

657
00:51:46,324 --> 00:51:47,909
That's fine.

658
00:51:48,740 --> 00:51:50,206
Next question.

659
00:51:51,039 --> 00:51:53,887
I could give you
10 billion won right now.

660
00:51:53,887 --> 00:51:55,518
Oh, really?

661
00:51:55,518 --> 00:51:57,909
You can split that with your friend.

662
00:51:57,909 --> 00:52:00,840
It's up to you how you split it.

663
00:52:00,840 --> 00:52:02,510
However...

664
00:52:02,510 --> 00:52:08,340
you need your friend's agreement in order
to receive that 10 billion won from me.

665
00:52:08,340 --> 00:52:10,516
How will you split it?

666
00:52:17,172 --> 00:52:19,876
I will split it 50:50.

667
00:52:21,141 --> 00:52:23,981
Are you saying you're not
confident in negotiating?

668
00:52:23,981 --> 00:52:27,570
Think of a way you could negotiate
to maximize your profits.

669
00:52:27,570 --> 00:52:29,903
Then answer again.

670
00:52:29,903 --> 00:52:32,811
How would that make me happy?

671
00:52:35,016 --> 00:52:36,963
You said the person was a friend.

672
00:52:36,963 --> 00:52:41,061
If I negotiated at my best
and split it 70:30 or 90:10

673
00:52:41,061 --> 00:52:43,507
my friendship with that person would end.

674
00:52:43,507 --> 00:52:46,360
Then I wouldn't be happy.

675
00:52:47,871 --> 00:52:52,541
I would choose to split it evenly
and be happy together.

676
00:53:06,791 --> 00:53:09,009
What is this strange mood?

677
00:53:15,117 --> 00:53:16,775
Good job.

678
00:53:26,007 --> 00:53:29,039
You did a good job today,
so I'll treat you to dinner.

679
00:53:29,039 --> 00:53:30,349
- Really?
- Yes.

680
00:53:30,349 --> 00:53:32,108
- Joon, you're paying?
- Of course.

681
00:53:32,108 --> 00:53:34,322
What should we eat?

682
00:53:42,318 --> 00:53:43,809
What is this?

683
00:53:43,809 --> 00:53:45,619
What should we do?

684
00:53:56,838 --> 00:53:59,842
When did you all prepare this?

685
00:54:06,637 --> 00:54:09,027
I'd better film this.

686
00:54:23,119 --> 00:54:25,170
<i>Good job!</i>

687
00:54:26,108 --> 00:54:29,166
<i>We are already so grateful.</i>

688
00:54:29,923 --> 00:54:32,657
<i>Even if you don't pass...</i>

689
00:54:34,246 --> 00:54:36,797
<i>we won't ever forget this.</i>

690
00:54:40,115 --> 00:54:43,443
You put in so much work for us.

691
00:54:48,923 --> 00:54:51,492
Hurry. Come on.

692
00:54:52,405 --> 00:54:54,407
Put it there.

693
00:54:54,967 --> 00:54:59,329
- Is it done?
- Okay.

694
00:54:59,329 --> 00:55:01,117
Wow.

695
00:55:02,710 --> 00:55:04,978
We're done. We're done.

696
00:55:07,083 --> 00:55:11,916
We're treating you to pork belly.

697
00:55:11,916 --> 00:55:13,119
Treating you!

698
00:55:13,119 --> 00:55:14,918
Let's go eat some hot pork belly!

699
00:55:14,918 --> 00:55:17,036
- Pork belly?
- Hot?

700
00:55:17,036 --> 00:55:18,686
- So hot.
- Oh...

701
00:55:18,686 --> 00:55:22,061
<i>Oh, so hot, so hot.
Oh, so hot, so hot.</i>

702
00:55:22,061 --> 00:55:25,246
<i>My heart is on fire because of you.</i>

703
00:55:25,246 --> 00:55:28,715
<i>Oh, so hot, so hot.
Oh, so hot, so hot.</i>

704
00:55:28,715 --> 00:55:31,094
<i>In front of love, I am melting.</i>

705
00:55:31,094 --> 00:55:32,572
Wow.

706
00:55:33,228 --> 00:55:36,409
They're not my family or friends.

707
00:55:36,409 --> 00:55:39,192
Not even the woman I love.

708
00:55:41,349 --> 00:55:44,416
Why are they making me so emotional?

709
00:55:45,369 --> 00:55:47,208
They're your colleagues.

710
00:55:51,650 --> 00:55:53,405
Yes, coming!

711
00:55:54,599 --> 00:55:57,447
<i>Oh, so hot, so hot.
Oh, so hot, so hot.</i>

712
00:55:57,447 --> 00:55:59,686
Why aren't you coming?

713
00:55:59,686 --> 00:56:01,458
I'm coming.

714
00:56:01,458 --> 00:56:06,248
<i>Oh, so hot, so hot.
Oh, so hot, so hot.</i>

715
00:56:13,228 --> 00:56:16,545
Then with a unanimous vote...

716
00:56:20,574 --> 00:56:22,300
<i>[Pass]</i>

717
00:56:26,550 --> 00:56:29,650
Next is Byun Hyuk.

718
00:56:37,112 --> 00:56:39,851
- Hey.
- Let's say a cheer.

719
00:56:39,851 --> 00:56:41,998
From battle to practice!

720
00:56:41,998 --> 00:56:44,057
From practice to battle!

721
00:56:44,057 --> 00:56:45,965
- Cheers!
- Cheers.

722
00:56:52,559 --> 00:56:54,418
Wow.

723
00:56:54,418 --> 00:56:56,548
Was soju always this good?

724
00:56:56,548 --> 00:56:58,518
It's much cleaner than liquor.

725
00:56:58,518 --> 00:57:00,728
Did you just figure that out now?

726
00:57:00,728 --> 00:57:03,057
Here. Have this.

727
00:57:10,432 --> 00:57:14,713
Mister Kim, thank you for
buying the pork belly today.

728
00:57:14,713 --> 00:57:16,945
